# Environment Setup Guidelines

## Python Environment
- Use Python 3.8 as specified in [setup.sh](mdc:setup.sh)
- Create virtual environment for isolation
- Install dependencies from [requirements.txt](mdc:requirements.txt)
- Use PyTorch 1.13 with CUDA 11.7 (or CPU-only)

## System Dependencies
Required packages (install via `setup_dev.sh`):
- `build-essential`
- `libboost-dev`
- `libboost-filesystem-dev`
- Python 3.8 and virtualenv

## Environment Activation
Always source the environment before development:
```bash
source setup.sh
```

## GPU Setup (Optional)
- CUDA 11.7 recommended
- CPU-only mode available for testing
- Different CUDA versions may yield different results

## Dependencies Management
- Core ML: PyTorch, NumPy, Gym
- Visualization: Matplotlib, Plotly, OpenCV
- Experiment tracking: TensorBoard, Optuna
- PCB tools: KiCad parsing utilities

## Installation Scripts
- [setup.sh](mdc:setup.sh) - Environment variables and paths
- [setup_dev.sh](mdc:setup_dev.sh) - Full development setup
- [install_tools_and_virtual_environment.sh](mdc:install_tools_and_virtual_environment.sh) - Automated installation

## Best Practices
- Always use virtual environments
- Pin dependency versions for reproducibility
- Test both CPU and GPU configurations
- Document any custom installations
